This paper is about Named Entity Disambiguation (NED), which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Information Retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of classifiers, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper uses Wikipedia as a knowledge-base, which is a type of database (cs.DB).
